This makes 7 deaths for me at his hands, so I'm going to have a friend help me with a necro and pull him to zone this weekend. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uthornyeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThornyEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 3:37:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4484.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tani</span><hr size=1> Well, I finally got the note last night. A friend made a level 1 necro and pulled Tani to zone, where I proceeded to pick him clean. Even then, it took three more attempts during the course of the weekend to get the note.<br>
<br>
Here are a few things I noticed:<br>
<br>
-- When you pull him out of the guild, he has just a few specific spots along the path that he will gate himself to once the puller is dead/zoned. Some of these spots (where he ends up halfway into a wall) cause a lot of PP attempts to end up with &quot;get closer&quot; messages, even though you're kissing up to him. This seems to be less of an issue right at the zone line.<br>
<br>
-- We found out that the puller pretty much needs to die at Tani's hands when at the zone line. If the puller zones out, Tani may gate to his nearest &quot;parked&quot; point along the path, but he can also gate all the way back to the rogue's guild. If the puller dies at the zone line, Tani stays at the zone line.<br>
<br>
-- Having Tani at the zone line isn't too bad if you need to zone in and are KoS. I was able to zone in and hit &quot;hide&quot; every single time I tried it, with him just an arm's length away, and he never aggroed me upon zoning.<br>
<br>
-- The bandage trick to see if he has the note doesn't work because sometimes you PP the bandage first, and sometimes last; it is a random chance as to what item you get from his inventory.<br>
